Did you know that 4.4 million potatoes go to waste every day in the UK? Inspired by @hellmannsuk and @channel4 show #CookCleverLessWaste I decided to use my leftover potatoes to make my simple, easy Crispy Smashed Potatoes recipe. Trust me, you’ll never waste a single potato ever again! 
 
Now, this isn't my typical IG reel recipe video, so watch this video all the way to the end to see how to make this incredibly easy dish!
 
Serves 4 as a side, or 2 as a main
 
15-20 baby potatoes
1-2 tbsp Hellmann's Vegan Mayo
1 tsp smoked paprika
1/4 lemon, juiced
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp black pepper
Pickled red onions
Fresh dill
Fresh chives
Extra virgin olive oil
 
* Bring the water in a saucepan to a boil. Add salt to the water then carefully drop the baby potatoes in the salted boiling water. Cook the potatoes for 15-20 minutes until soft then drain.
* Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 200C.
* Gently press the potatoes until the peel breaks and place them on a baking sheet. Drizzle a bit of oil, a pinch of salt and black pepper and bake for 20 minutes until golden and crispy.
* In the almost empty jar of Hellmann's vegan mayo, add the smoked paprika in lemon juice and shake for a few seconds until the ingredients are mixed well. Add a few dollops of the smoked lemon mayo to the potatoes, add the pickled red onions and fresh herbs. 
 
Enjoy! 
 
To get started your food waste journey, check our Hellmann’s Food Waste Handbook here - https://www.hellmanns.com/uk/secure/signup.html
 
What’s more, as part of @hellmannsuk fight against food waste, Hellmann's has donated an equivalent of 40,000 meals to a charitable food redistributor @fareshareuk.

AD  Live Q&A with @tetrapak (20 minutes)⁣
 ⁣
From the role of packaging to reducing food waste and the environment, I have a quick chat with Tetra Pak's Director of Business Insights & Analytics to understand how Tetra Pak's is improving the world of packaging solutions.⁣
 ⁣
Covid-19 has displaced the environment as the number one consumer concern. Food safety and food security have risen significantly as a result, and trying to balance these concerns with our worries for the environment are creating a dilemma.⁣
 ⁣
Health is now connected to heightened issues of food safety and hygiene; two-thirds of consumers said that being healthy is being safe. Improving food safety was cited as the number one priority for manufacturers. ⁣
 ⁣
Transparency is key, with almost three in five consumers saying they want to know all they can about product production.⁣
 ⁣
Anything we didn’t cover? Let me know what you would ask Tetra Pak in the comments below.⁣
 ⁣
@TetraPak #TetraPakIndex

in collaboration with @SmartEnergyGB and @homebase_uk. There are tons of ways to make your home super green and more efficient, from getting a smart meter installed to monitor and reduce your energy use through to wasting less food.⁣
⁣
✅My 3 super green recipes today have been inspired by Homebase’s new Green Aisle in collaboration with Smart Energy GB, where you can find a whole host of sustainable home improvement products, as well as information on smart meters.⁣
⁣
Leftover Spinach Tortillas⁣
240g flour⁣
1 tsp salt⁣
90-100ml water⁣
⁣
Leftover Herb Hummus⁣
1 tin of chickpeas, reserve chickpea water⁣
A handful of mixed herbs⁣
2 tbsp olive oil⁣
1/2 lemon, juiced⁣
1 tsp salt⁣
1/2 tsp black pepper⁣
1 tbsp tahini⁣
Splash of chickpea water⁣
⁣
Green Doughnuts⁣
A handful of leftover spinach⁣
200g flour⁣
80g sugar⁣
1 tsp baking powder⁣
1/4 tsp salt⁣
180ml plant-based milk⁣
60ml chickpea water⁣
2 tbsp apple sauce ⁣
1 tsp vanilla extract⁣
⁣
Hope you enjoyed my 3 super green recipes, and also do make sure to visit The Green Aisle at a Homebase store near you! #TheGreenAisle⁣

Here’s a snippet from last week‘s conversation with @mileycyrus on her @instagram live show. ⁣
⁣
We talked all things zero waste, our issues with food waste and how someone could be more resourceful and create less waste in the kitchen. ⁣
⁣
I even made Miley a really simple recipe that uses up ingredients you most likely have in your kitchen right now, or if you don’t, they’re fairly accessible and easy to get hold of. The full recipe video is over on my @youtube channel right now. Check it out!⁣
⁣
Did you get a chance to watch me go live with Miley? ⁣
⁣

Back on Instagram…

Over 3 weeks ago I made these veg/herb cubes. I had a bunch of herbs and garlic that were going off and thought “there must be way to use them later...”

For those of you who are wasting herbs and garlic, you can blend them up with water until smooth. Pour the mixture into ice cube trays - or into reusable cupcake moulds. Freeze, and use them in any sort of soup, stew, curry or pasta dish.

Add veg/herb cube to a saucepan over medium heat. Melt until all the water has evaporated then add the tomatoes and olive oil stirring occasionally, cook for 8 minutes until tomatoes have reduced in size.

Cook the pasta according to the package instructions amd strain.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce, stir to combine for 1 minute over a low heat.

Serve pasta to plate or bowl with garlic breadcrumbs, herbs and salt.

Fluffy Potato Rolls

UK’s #1 most wasted food:
4.4 million potatoes are wasted at home each day.

Save your potatoes and make this recipe now!

👇🏼Save, share, comment

Makes 12 rolls

270g cooked potatoes
mashed, skins on

296ml water
warm

8g dried active yeast

625g flour

2 tsp salt

1 tsp sugar

6 tbsp vegan butter

Instructions
1. Whisk water, yeast and sugar until foamy then let it sit for 5 minutes.
2. Meanwhile (if needed, unless the mashed potatoes are leftovers) mash potatoes with the skins on.
3. In a large mixing bowl, add flour, salt, yeast mixture and 4 tbsp butter. Mix well until all the ingredients are incorporated and the dough is slightly smooth. Cover with a kitchen towel until double in size or for 1 hour.
4. Sprinkle flour to a surface. Punch dough to deflate. Roll dough out and divide into 12 balls. Place each ball into a greased baking dish 13x9in or 33x22cm to prove for another 30-45 minutes.
5. Pre heat oven to 200c/425f
6. Brush the remaining vegan butter on the tops of each ball of dough and bake for 25 minutes.

🍝Speedy Spaghetti (5 ingredients)

A quick meal with minimal ingredients. Get creative with the food you have in your fridge. 

👋🏼Do you want to see more recipes that are under 20 minutes or recipes with minimal ingredients?

👇🏼Cook now or save for later

Serves 2
Prep: 5 minutes
Cook: 15 minutes

225g spaghetti 
1 red onion, thinly sliced
130g puy lentils
1 courgette, julienne
1 tin (400g) chopped tomatoes
1/2 tsp dried rosemary 
1/2 tsp dried thyme
Salt 
Black pepper

Instructions
1. In a frying pan over medium heat add some oil, then add the red onion and saute for a few minutes until soft.
2. Add the courgette, lentils and seasonings and stir for a few minutes.
3. Add the chopped tomatoes, stir and simmer for a few minutes.
4. In a saucepan with boiling water add some salt and then add your spaghetti and cook for 9-12 or until al dente.
5. Add the cooked pasta to the sauce, stir and serve.

🥦stem fried rice

Quick and satisfyingly easy to make. You’ll never waste broccoli stems ever again. Try this recipe and let me know how it goes for you!

❤️Save and share this recipe!

Serves 2
Cook time: 25 minutes

135g white rice
240g shiitake mushrooms
1 thumb size piece of ginger, grated
4 garlic cloves, thinly sliced
1 large broccoli stem, grated
1 tbsp soy sauce or tamari
1/2 tsp red chili flakes
Carrot, shredded
Red cabbage, shredded
Coriander, chopped
Chives, chopped
Lemon juice

Instructions
1. Bring a saucepan of water to a boil. Add the rice and simmer for 10-15 minutes until rice is cooked, occasionally stirring - *double the amount of water to rice.
2. Add some oil to a frying pan on medium heat and stir in the garlic and ginger for one minute before adding the mushrooms.
3. Stir and cook for 3-5 minutes until the mushrooms are soft. Next, add the broccoli stem and cook for another 3-5 minutes.
4. Add the cooked rice and soy sauce.
5. Stir for another 3 minutes, occasionally stirring. If rice sticks to the frying pan, add a splash of water or oil.
6. Add fried rice to a plate and finish with an assortment of garnishes.

🥞The best pancakes ever!

Fluffy, delicious and easy-to-make pancakes have your name all over them this weekend. 

Comment your favourite pancake toppings 👇🏼👇🏼👇🏼

Makes 10

150g buckwheat flour
100g gluten-free plain flour
360ml non-dairy milk
1 tbsp apple cider vinegar
1 tsp neutral oil 
2 tsp caster sugar
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
3/4 tsp baking soda 
1/2 tsp salt
1 tbsp chia seeds

Vegan buttermilk:
Mix the non-dairy milk and apple cider vinegar in a bowl and set aside for 10 minutes. 

Meanwhile, mix the remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl. 

Add the vegan buttermilk and stir until combined. 

Pour batter to a heated frying pan. Cook for 2 minutes on each side. 

Add your favourite toppings!

🥒cucumber gazpacho

Need something cool & refreshing? You need to try this! It’s easy, delicious + no waste too!

Here’s how to make it!

Serves 2 or 4

1 large cucumber
1/2 avocado
1/2 lime juice
1 tbsp olive oil
1 leek, just the green top
2 tbsp plant based yoghurt
Cold water (see recipe below)
2 sprigs of basil, plus stems
Salt
Black pepper

1. Place the entire cucumber into the blender - no need to peel or remove seeds.
2. Blend with the remaining ingredients.
3. Slowly and carefully pour the water through the top of the blender (if possible). Only enough water until the consistency is smooth and creamy. If too thick, add more water.
4. Chill in the fridge for up to one hour or overnight
5. Garnish with extra slices of cucumber, toasted seeds and micro greens

Enjoy!

🍝Just another one-pot pasta recipe…

🇮🇹I know this isn’t traditional, and my Italian grandmother would be upset…fortunately she doesn’t have Instagram. 

Save this recipe
Share it
Now cook it!

Serves 2
Cool Time 10-15 minutes 

185g spaghetti
1 tbsp olive oil
2 garlic cloves, diced
1 large handful spinach 
115g pre-cooked lentils
400g crush tomatoes
590ml water or veg stock 
Handful of basil
Salt
Black pepper
Red chili flakes

Fry the garlic for 1-2 minutes
Add tomatoes and stir
Add remaining ingredients
Carefully stirring (don’t break the pasta), cook for 10 minutes on medium/ medium high heat
Serve with fresh basil

Enjoy 😊

One Pot 🍋 Pasta 

Super simple, easy, minimal ingredients and it’s ONE POT which means less washing up!

Save it
Share it
Cook it

Serves 2
300g rigatoni
1 onion, diced
3 garlic cloves, chopped
240ml hot water
(400g)1 tin full-fat coconut milk 
1 lemon, juice and zest
1-2 tbsp olive oil
Salt
Black pepper
Red chilli flakes

1️⃣ sauté onions in a frying pan for 5-7 minutes. 
2️⃣ add garlic and stir for 1 minute.
3️⃣ add the remaining ingredients and cook on a medium high heat for 15 minutes - occasionally stirring.

Serve with leafy greens and/or herbs

2 tsp brown sugar

crushed chilli

Let’s make my easy chickpea coconut curry

Serves 2-4
Cook time 25 minutes

300g cooked chickpeas
1 onion, diced
1-2 tbsp coriander stems, chopped
4 garlic cloves, chopped
1 red bell pepper, sliced
130g carrots, chopped
25g ginger, grated
400g coconut milk
1/2 tsp turmeric powder
1 tsp cumin powder
1/4 tsp red chili flakes
1 tsp garam masala
Pinch of salt 
Black pepper
Fresh coriander
Lime juice
Red onion, thinly sliced

1️⃣Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Stir in onion, coriander stems and bay leaf. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is golden on the edges, about 5-10 minutes.
2️⃣Add garlic and ginger; cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes, stirring frequently. 
3️⃣Stir in chickpeas and red bell pepper, about 2 minutes, occasionally stirring. Stir in turmeric powder, ground cumin, red chili flakes, garam masala, salt and black pepper; cook for an additional 30-45 seconds. Stir in the coconut milk and add the carrot. Bring to a simmer and continue to simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 
4️⃣Serve over rice, couscous, quinoa or noodles, if you like, and top with cilantro, thinly sliced red onions, and a squeeze of lime juice.
